The Emir of Zazzau, Ambassador Ahmad Nuhu Bamalli has been appointed as the Patron SABIL Charitable International Organisation. His appointment followed the demise of the former Emir of Zazzau, Dr. Shehu Idris who was the Grand Patron of the organisation. The President of the organisation, Halimatu Saadiya Abdu while speaking when the executive members of the organisation paid a visit to the traditional ruler said the association accepted to maintain its stand and make the new emir its patron. Responding, the Emir of Zazzau, expressed his appreciation to the organisation for recognising him worthy to be its patron.